Of course I do.

90
00:07:17,312 --> 00:07:20,893
They could care less about me anyway.

91
00:07:23,963 --> 00:07:25,976
Remember at the demo

92
00:07:26,046 --> 00:07:28,761
when we went to turn it on and it wouldn’t turn on ?

93
00:07:28,762 --> 00:07:30,089
Gordon…

94
00:07:30,814 --> 00:07:36,471
It’s like, 1979 was good, but then 1980 came

95
00:07:36,472 --> 00:07:40,140
and it was like, whoa…

96
00:07:40,827 --> 00:07:43,766
what happened, you know ?

97
00:07:44,411 --> 00:07:48,406
What I know is that you need to be at work in four hours.

98
00:07:48,407 --> 00:07:50,089
Four.

99
00:07:52,413 --> 00:07:55,878
Then your dad… your dad said,

100
00:07:55,879 --> 00:07:58,441
“We can’t lend you any more.”

101
00:07:58,723 --> 00:08:01,028
And he wasn’t being mean.

102
00:08:01,029 --> 00:08:04,538
He was just in his kitchen looking at me,

103
00:08:04,539 --> 00:08:08,913
and I said, “Okay, Gary.”

104
00:08:08,914 --> 00:08:11,264
You’re drunk, so the best thing

105
00:08:11,265 --> 00:08:14,019
you could do right now is to shut up.

106
00:08:18,029 --> 00:08:20,935
[ clicks ]
— I know what IBM is.

107
00:08:22,964 --> 00:08:24,162
I also know what IBM ain’t,

108
00:08:24,163 --> 00:08:26,777
and everything that ain’t IBM
is cheaper, faster, and better,

109
00:08:26,778 --> 00:08:28,130
and that’s what this company lives by.

110
00:08:28,131 --> 00:08:29,507
Well, John, that’s what Hitachi thought.

111
00:08:29,508 --> 00:08:31,800
And Burroughs and NCR

112
00:08:31,801 --> 00:08:33,200
and Honeywell and Control Data.

113
00:08:33,201 --> 00:08:35,607
No, I know all the companies that IBM has crushed,

114
00:08:35,608 --> 00:08:37,919
and Cardiff Electric ain’t one of ’em. It won’t be.

115
00:08:37,920 --> 00:08:39,576
You sound pretty sure about that.

116
00:08:39,577 --> 00:08:41,911
[ laughs ] Look at you.

117
00:08:42,198 --> 00:08:45,158
Same suit, different tie.

118
00:08:46,275 --> 00:08:50,038
You know, Dallas is a long way from Armonk, New York, son.

119
00:08:50,039 --> 00:08:52,066
— That’s no accident.
— I couldn’t agree with you more.

120
00:08:52,067 --> 00:08:54,877
Maybe I’m a guy who’s done doing business like that.

121
00:08:54,878 --> 00:08:57,252
Maybe I see Cardiff Electric as a mid-major

122
00:08:57,253 --> 00:08:58,480
ready to take the jump

123
00:08:58,481 --> 00:09:00,538
and myself as the heavy hitter you need

124
00:09:00,539 --> 00:09:03,942
to legitimize your sales force, this company, this region.

125
00:09:03,943 --> 00:09:07,665
I just need someone to come in here and
blow the balls off the numbers, Joe.

126
00:09:07,666 --> 00:09:10,473
I will tell you this… it’s
system software, straight up.

127
00:09:10,474 --> 00:09:13,192
No application, no next-gen PC garbage.

128
00:09:13,193 --> 00:09:15,272
It ain’t sexy, but it sure as
hell make us some serious money.

129
00:09:15,273 --> 00:09:18,077
— Then I’m your guy.
[ scoffs ] Don’t know if I see it.

130
00:09:18,078 --> 00:09:20,090
You got East Coast corporate written all over ya.

131
00:09:20,091 --> 00:09:22,268
Don’t like East Coast corporate.

132
00:09:22,269 --> 00:09:26,269
Hell, hotshot, you didn’t bring in a damn resume.

133
00:09:29,766 --> 00:09:31,196
[ briefcase latches click ]

134
00:09:33,869 --> 00:09:37,385
— And what is this ? What am I looking at ?
— My W-2.

135
00:09:37,674 --> 00:09:40,452
— Box one is my last reported income at IBM.
— Whoo-hoo.

136
00:09:40,453 --> 00:09:43,672
It’s also what 200% of quota looks like.

137
00:09:44,833 --> 00:09:46,464
The golden circle.

138
00:09:46,713 --> 00:09:50,229
I’ll break numbers. I always do.

139
00:09:51,743 --> 00:09:53,701
[ laughs ]

140
00:09:54,956 --> 00:09:57,975
You answer to me. I’m SVP of sales,

141
00:09:57,976 --> 00:10:02,530
so you’re dog shit around here until you close a deal.

142
00:10:02,531 --> 00:10:04,918
— Do you understand ?
— I do.

143
00:10:04,919 --> 00:10:08,412
All right: “Do.” Good.

144
00:10:08,413 --> 00:10:11,448
Well, we’re married.

145
00:10:12,708 --> 00:10:15,838
You may now go break your numbers, darlin’.

146
00:10:44,816 --> 00:10:47,673
Woman on radio: — <i>… free and clear
through Lewisville and Carrollton,</i>

147
00:10:47,674 --> 00:10:49,406
<i>but starting to slow down…</i>

148
00:10:49,494 --> 00:10:51,199
[ engine belt squeaking ]

149
00:10:51,200 --> 00:10:53,119
Hey.

150
00:10:53,120 --> 00:10:54,311
[ horn honks ]

151
00:10:55,333 --> 00:10:56,714
A-16.

152
00:10:58,749 --> 00:11:02,516
Hey, that’s me. That’s my spot, A-16.

153
00:11:09,074 --> 00:11:12,884
Woman on radio: — <i>… high from
Love Field today is 86…</i>

154
00:11:30,814 --> 00:11:32,653
[ clicks ]

155
00:11:36,646 --> 00:11:38,202
MacMillan: — A-16 !

156
00:11:39,029 --> 00:11:40,820
A-16.

157
00:11:42,415 --> 00:11:46,712
— You’re my SE for this sales call.
— Oh, fantastic.

158
00:11:46,713 --> 00:11:49,972
We’ll take my car, it’s closer.

159
00:11:50,776 --> 00:11:52,575
MacMillan: — You know the truth is are system’s

160
00:11:52,576 --> 00:11:54,910
are outperforming every top seller in the market.

161
00:11:54,911 --> 00:11:57,199
— What about IBM ?
— IBM is IBM,

162
00:11:57,200 --> 00:11:58,893
but we’re neck and neck and we’re cheaper.

163
00:11:58,894 --> 00:12:02,081
Technically. The difference in cost is negligible.

164
00:12:02,106 --> 00:12:05,319
It just seems you guys at Cardiff think
you’ve built yourselves a fancy race car

165
00:12:05,320 --> 00:12:07,018
that deserves and outrageous price tag.

166
00:12:07,019 --> 00:12:08,895
And we get no Big Blue guarantee.

167
00:12:08,896 --> 00:12:11,006
I don’t think there is such a thing.

168
00:12:11,506 --> 00:12:13,019
Well, they had me fooled.

169
00:12:13,020 --> 00:12:15,015
[ man laughs ]
— Me, too.

170
00:12:16,191 --> 00:12:18,758
I worked there.

171
00:12:20,416 --> 00:12:22,506
I grew up there.

172
00:12:22,763 --> 00:12:25,872
And I was brought up to believe that the work we did,

173
00:12:25,873 --> 00:12:28,935
the things we built were the
singular contribution to computers

174
00:12:28,936 --> 00:12:30,586
that history would remember.

175
00:12:30,686 --> 00:12:32,684
And I believed it for a long time.

176
00:12:33,023 --> 00:12:36,320
For a long time, it was true.

177
00:12:38,055 --> 00:12:42,451
Nobody ever got ﬁred for buying an IBM, right ?

178
00:12:42,685 --> 00:12:45,358
What a fearful way to do business.

179
00:12:45,842 --> 00:12:49,025
You’ve made just enough safe choices

180
00:12:49,026 --> 00:12:52,137
to stay alive, but not enough to matter.

181
00:12:52,364 --> 00:12:54,503
Is that what you want ?

182
00:12:54,820 --> 00:12:57,495
You can be more.

183
00:12:57,496 --> 00:13:01,395
You want to be more, don’t you ?

184
00:13:02,662 --> 00:13:05,787
The window of opportunity is closing.

185
00:13:05,788 --> 00:13:08,183
This is your chance.

186
00:13:08,184 --> 00:13:10,851
This is not about not losing.

187
00:13:10,852 --> 00:13:15,571
This is about you ﬁnally having the conﬁdence

188
00:13:15,794 --> 00:13:20,431
to walk out on the ledge and know
that you’re not going to fall.

189
00:13:21,811 --> 00:13:25,071
Are we still talking about systems software here ?

190
00:13:25,072 --> 00:13:27,555
Amen, let’s get this guy another drink.

191
00:13:27,585 --> 00:13:30,782
I’m not going to apologize for
caring about your business,

192
00:13:30,783 --> 00:13:32,813
even if the people who work for you don’t.

193
00:13:33,998 --> 00:13:36,601
I’ll ask you one more time.

194
00:13:37,864 --> 00:13:40,406
Are you ready to be more ?

195
00:13:53,347 --> 00:13:58,236
— There’s also free install…
— Gordon, please.

196
00:14:02,947 --> 00:14:05,412
I’ll think about it.

197
00:14:16,845 --> 00:14:20,566
Look, it’s better than a ﬂat-out no.

198
00:14:22,529 --> 00:14:26,354
Hey, man, look, Applied Data hasn’t
bought jack-all from anyone in years.

199
00:14:26,355 --> 00:14:28,203
You did a solid job explaining the software,

200
00:14:28,204 --> 00:14:30,571
but I need you to do me one favor.

201
00:14:30,572 --> 00:14:31,248
Okay.

202
00:14:31,249 --> 00:14:34,163
Next time I move to close, this is what you do.

203
00:14:34,164 --> 00:14:37,767
— Okay, what ?
— You shut up !

204
