214
00:15:13,912 --> 00:15:15,475
Well, what’s wrong with it ?

215
00:15:15,476 --> 00:15:17,789
— It won’t turn on.
— Joanie did it.

216
00:15:17,790 --> 00:15:21,641
Uh-uh, Haley did it. She was playing with her blocks…

217
00:15:21,642 --> 00:15:22,573
Let’s see.

218
00:15:25,519 --> 00:15:28,297
Joanie’s Speak & Spell won’t turn on.

219
00:15:29,280 --> 00:15:31,199
Joanie: — Pressing “on” makes it go.

220
00:15:32,446 --> 00:15:33,646
Okay.

221
00:15:34,443 --> 00:15:37,222
— Are you gonna ﬁx it ?
— I’m gonna try.

222
00:15:37,488 --> 00:15:39,353
Did it give you any good words ?

223
00:15:39,965 --> 00:15:42,069
Did it stump you at all ?

224
00:15:42,131 --> 00:15:43,408
No.

225
00:15:44,307 --> 00:15:45,274
Okay.

226
00:15:45,898 --> 00:15:47,926
Joanie: — She was throwing her blocks at it.

227
00:15:48,193 --> 00:15:50,249
Haley: — But you did it. You were pressing “on.”

228
00:15:50,250 --> 00:15:52,207
— I don’t care who broke it.
— That probably breaked it.

229
00:15:52,208 --> 00:15:54,314
— I’m just gonna get it ﬁxed, okay ?
— No.

230
00:15:54,777 --> 00:15:59,035
[ sighs ] Okay, girls, other room, please.

231
00:15:59,249 --> 00:16:01,772
[ both grumble ]
— Please ? Thank you.

232
00:16:16,653 --> 00:16:18,105
[ sighs ]

233
00:16:19,965 --> 00:16:23,160
You want to take a look and see what’s wrong with that ?

234
00:16:23,161 --> 00:16:25,169
They make that where you work, not where I do.

235
00:16:25,170 --> 00:16:28,624
Okay, Gordon, do you want to maybe get me the salt ?

236
00:16:28,625 --> 00:16:30,063
Maybe you could reach into the cabinet

237
00:16:30,064 --> 00:16:31,486
about seven inches from your head,

238
00:16:31,487 --> 00:16:33,478
take out the salt and put it in my hand

239
00:16:33,479 --> 00:16:34,582
so I can ﬁnish cooking this.

240
00:16:34,583 --> 00:16:36,918
Do you think you could at least get me the salt ?

241
00:16:40,992 --> 00:16:42,420
Here’s the salt.

242
00:16:44,791 --> 00:16:46,271
Thank you.

243
00:17:04,995 --> 00:17:07,046
[ object slaps ]
— A-16.

244
00:17:09,165 --> 00:17:11,881
— What is this ?
— Page 33.

245
00:17:12,753 --> 00:17:15,367
— Man, if you think it’s funny…
— Page 33.

246
00:17:15,368 --> 00:17:17,366
I’m not in the mood, all right ?

247
00:17:17,367 --> 00:17:19,768
Why don’t you go blow-dry your
hair some more or something ?

248
